Leber hereditary optic neuropathy, autosomal recessive

mucopolysaccharidosis or mucopolysaccharidosis-like disorder
definition: Any disease that presents as a mucopolysaccharidosis or mucopolysaccharidosis-like disorder.

label: occupational disorder
definition: Any disorder that is realized in response to an exposure to occupation.

label: port-wine nevi-mega cisterna magna-hydrocephalus syndrome
definition: A rare developmental defect during embryogenesis syndrome characterized by a glabellar capillary malformation, congenital communicating hydrocephalus, and posterior fossa brain abnormalities, including Dandy-Walker malformation, cerebellar vermis agenesis, and mega cisterna magna. Seizures are occasionally associated. There have been no further descriptions in the literature since 1979.

label: intrahepatic cholestasis of pregnancy
definition: A cholestatic disorder characterized by (i) pruritus with onset in the second or third trimester of pregnancy, (ii) elevated serum aminotransferases and bile acid levels, and (iii) spontaneous relief of signs and symptoms within two to three weeks after delivery.

label: B-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia with t(1;19)(q23;p13.3); E2A-PBX1 (TCF3-PBX1)
definition: A B-cell acute leukemia characterized by the presence of lymphoblasts that carry a translocation between the E2A gene on chromosome 19 and the PBX1 gene on chromosome 1. It occurs in children and less often in adults.

label: infectious discitis
definition: An infection of the intervertebral disc space.

label: staphylococcus discitis
definition: Discitis caused by infection with Staphylococcus.

label: escherichia coli discitis
definition: Discitis caused by infection with Escherichia coli.

label: streptococcus pneumoniae discitis
definition: Discitis caused by infection with Streptococcus pneumoniae.

label: salmonella discitis
definition: Discitis caused by infection with Salmonella.

label: fungal discitis
definition: Discitis caused by infection with fungi.
